<P>
TENNIS ROUNDUP; HEALTHY SAMPRAS WINS FIRST TOURNAMENT SINCE WIMBLEDON 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Pete Sampras used his big serve to complete a perfect tune-up for the ATP Tour 
World Championships, beating Magnus Larsson, 7-6 (7-5), 6-4, Sunday and 
retaining his $1.1 million European Community Championship title in Antwerp, 
Belgium. 
</P>
<P>
 The $3 million tour-ending event featuring the top eight players in the world 
begins Tuesday in Frankfurt, Germany. 
</P>
<P>
 Sampras, the world's No. 1 player, won a record ninth tournament this season, 
his first since Wimbledon. He didn't lose a set during the week and proved he 
is at his peak again after injuries slowed him this summer. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Anke Huber of Germany hung on to defeat Mary Pierce of France, 6-0, 6-7 (4-7), 
7-5, for the championship of the $750,000 Virginia Slims of Philadelphia. Huber 
nearly blew a 4-0 lead in the third set before she settled down for her third 
victory of the season. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Alexander Volkov of Russia won the $1.1 million Kremlin Cup tournament in 
Moscow, defeating Chuck Adams of the United States, 6-2, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Alex Corretja of Spain won his first ATP Tour title, defeating Javier Frana of 
Argentina, 6-3, 5-7, 7-6 (7-5), in the final of the $313,000 Topper Open in 
Buenos Aires. 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 UCLA's Jane Chi, ranked No. 2 in the NCAA, defeated teammate Keri Phebus, 6-4, 
6-4, in the final of the Southern California Women's Tennis Regional Tournament 
at UC Irvine. 
</P>
