<HEADLINE>
<P>
HUNTER LIVES ON EDGE OF LUCK AS KNIFE STOPS BULLET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The knife a hunter kept in his shirt pocket stopped a bullet from hitting his 
heart. 
</P>
<P>
 Howard Lemere escaped with only a cracked rib after another hunter 
accidentally shot him. The bullet hit the large hunting knife in his shirt's 
upper left-hand pocket. 
</P>
<P>
 Lemere, 28, and a friend were hunting deer Wednesday when they flushed a 
coyote. A hunter nearby took three shots, one which hit Lemere. The shooter got 
into his car and sped off, Lemere said. The Renville County sheriff's office is 
investigating. 
</P>
