<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; BEACH CLEANUP PLAN PROPOSED FOR SPRING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ever wanted a stretch of beach for your very own? Yours to plaster your name 
all over -- and yours to clean up? 
</P>
<P>
 Ventura may offer a bargain deal on public sand and ocean in the near future. 
</P>
<P>
 The Adopt-a-Beach program would allow individuals and companies to claim a 
length of public turf and erect a sign on that beach with their names. 
</P>
<P>
 The sponsor would then take on all responsibility for keeping that stretch 
free of trash and other debris. 
</P>
<P>
 "We've had interest expressed from a lot of businesses about doing something 
different at the beaches," said Bill Byerts, Ventura's parks manager. 
</P>
<P>
 Byerts said the city has hired a consultant to organize the program, which 
officials hope will be in place by late spring. CONSTANCE SOMMER 
</P>
</TEXT>
