<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: CAMARILLO; FIRE IN GARAGE CAUSES $125,000 IN DAMAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Smoldering ashes in a trash can inside the garage of a house near Camarillo 
started a fire that caused $125,000 in damage early Sunday, fire officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 A smoke alarm woke up residents of the Deseo Avenue house about 4 a.m. Sunday, 
when flames from the trash can spread to the garage, Ventura County Fire 
Department officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire was mostly limited to the garage, which received about $65,000 in 
structural damage, officials estimated. A small corner of the house also 
incurred damage, investigators said. The fire also destroyed about $60,000 in 
property, including a new van and a Honda Accord, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 No one was seriously injured in the blaze, which took about 40 firefighters 
more than an hour to extinguish. 
</P>
<P>
 One firefighter was treated at St. John's Pleasant Valley Hospital for a minor 
hand injury and was later released, a Fire Department spokeswoman said. JEFF 
McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
