<HEADLINE>
<P>
TEAMS SEARCH MATILIJA CANYON FOR 2 HIKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ventura County Sheriff's Department search-and-rescue teams spent Sunday 
combing Matilija Canyon looking for two hikers who failed to report Saturday 
after a day hike in the heavily wooded canyon north of Ojai. 
</P>
<P>
 After James Seebirt, 56, of Ojai and Bill Hallfish, 59, of Camarillo failed to 
return home after sundown Saturday, family members notified authorities, who 
quickly began organizing a search of the canyon, Sheriff's Lt. Gary Backman 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The first search teams hit the trails about 2 a.m. Sunday, with a helicopter 
unit joining them at dawn, Backman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Donna Seebirt, James Seebirt's wife, said her husband and Hallfish are 
experienced hikers who recently completed a long hike of the Half-Dome area at 
Yosemite National Park. 
</P>
<P>
 "Both Jim and Bill are in great shape and have been hiking together for 
years," Donna Seebirt said. "They know how to handle themselves in rough 
terrain. I'm confident they're OK." J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
