<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; 2 TEEN-AGERS SHOT AT, ESCAPE INJURY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two teen-agers escaped injury early Sunday after being shot at near Foothill 
Park in Simi Valley, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Mathis Smith, 18, and an unidentified 17-year-old were in a car parked in the 
1800 block of Charing Court about 3:30 a.m. Sunday when they were approached by 
two alleged gang members, according to police. 
</P>
<P>
 One of the suspects pulled out a handgun and fired at the car, shattering the 
side windows of the vehicle, but missing the two teen-agers, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 The suspects fled the area, officials said. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
