<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; KUWAITI TO SPEAK TO WORLD AFFAIRS 
GROUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kuwait's ambassador to the United States will visit Ventura County on Saturday 
to meet with Port Hueneme-based Seabees who served in the Persian Gulf War and 
local business people whose companies do business with the tiny Arab emirate. 
</P>
<P>
 Mohammed Sabah Al-Salim Al-Sabah will be the guest of the Ventura County World 
Affairs Council at the North Ranch Country Club in Thousand Oaks, said Cindy 
Cooke, the council's executive director.Al-Sabah will discuss his country's 
ongoing tense relations with neighboring Iraq, Cooke said. 
</P>
<P>
 The breakfast meeting will start at 10:30 a.m. The public is invited to attend 
the meeting. Advance tickets for members are $15, $20 for non-members. Tickets 
at the door are $25. For information, call 449-9953. J. E. MITCHELL 
</P>
</TEXT>
