DRIVER ARRESTED IN FATAL ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 23-year-old Sylmar man was arrested Sunday after the car he was driving spun 
out of control and smashed into a light pole and brick wall, killing an 
18-year-old passenger, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Fabian Perez of Sylmar died at the scene of the 2 a.m. accident.He was a 
passenger in the back seat of a Chevrolet Camaro headed south on Woodman Avenue 
near San Jose Street, said Los Angeles Police Officer Connie Fisher. 
</P>
<P>
 Witnesses told police that the car, driven by Tony Maraz, 23, of Sylmar, 
crossed into oncoming lanes, then ran off the road and hit a light pole and 
block wall, Fisher said. 
</P>
<P>
 Maraz and another passenger, Gilbert Diaz, 18, of San Fernando received minor 
injuries, she said. 
</P>
<P>
 Maraz was arrested on suspicion of manslaughter and is being held in lieu of 
$35,000 bail, Fisher said. 
</P>
