<P>
2 KILLED, 3 INJURED IN SYLMAR CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEANNETTE REGALADO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two men were killed Sunday when their car slammed into a fire hydrant and then 
struck a light pole, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Three other men in the same car were critically injured in the 4:50 a.m. 
accident on San Fernando Road near Paddock Street in Sylmar, said Los Angeles 
Police Officer Gary Weller. 
</P>
<P>
 The driver, Jesus Martinez Cardenas, 21, of Sylmar was traveling south on San 
Fernando Road when he lost control of his Plymouth Colt, leveled a fire 
hydrant, then struck a pole, Weller said. Cardenas died at the scene. 
</P>
<P>
 One of his passengers, Jose Martinez Hernandez, 33, also of Sylmar was taken 
to Harbor-UCLA Medical Center, where he died, said a Los Angeles County coroner 
spokesman. 
</P>
<P>
 The three other passengers, all men in their 20s, were taken to local 
hospitals and are all listed in critical condition, he said. 
</P>
