<HEADLINE>
<P>
SANDERS (237 YARDS) STEALS SHOW; NFC: HE COMES THROUGH WITH BEST GAME AS A PRO 
TO LEAD THE LIONS OVER BUCCANEERS, 14-9. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Barry Sanders almost defies description. 
</P>
<P>
 But Tampa Bay rookie Errict Rhett gave it a try after the Detroit Lions' 14-9 
victory over the Buccaneers Sunday night. 
</P>
<P>
 "Not only can I not do the things Barry does, I can't even describe them," 
Rhett said. 
</P>
<P>
 Sanders, the NFL's leading rusher, had his best game as a pro against the 
Buccaneers, rushing 26 times for a career-high 237 yards -- an even 200 in the 
second half. 
</P>
<P>
 It was only the second game of more than 200 yards for Sanders; the other came 
in 1991 when he ran for 220 against Minnesota. 
</P>
<P>
 "God ain't made a better back in this lifetime," Lion Coach Wayne Fontes said. 
"Maybe one will come along someday. But it hasn't happened yet." 
</P>
<P>
 Sanders has rushed for 100 yards or more eight times against the Buccaneers. 
In the last five, Sanders had burned the Buccaneers for 122, 130, 187, 166 and 
237 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 Sanders now leads the NFL with 1,319 yards. This is Sanders' best 10-game 
start of his career. His best start prior to this season came in 1993, when he 
gained 1,052 yards after his first 10 games. 
</P>
<P>
 At this rate, he is on pace to gain 2,110 yards. 
</P>
<P>
 "I can't say I never think about it," Sanders said. "But it's not part of my 
game preparation. I don't want to complicate things any more than they already 
are. It would be wonderful to reach that mark. But I'm determined not to go 
into each game focusing on that." 
</P>
<P>
 Sanders needed the big night to keep from being upstaged by Rhett, who rushed 
25 times for 112 yards. It was the first time a Tampa Bay runner gained more 
than 100 since Reggie Cobb ran for 113 against Detroit on Oct. 3, 1993. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the fifth consecutive loss for Tampa Bay (2-8). 
</P>
<P>
 The Lions, behind the running of Sanders and passing of Dave Krieg, scored two 
touchdowns in the third quarter, one on a one-yard run by Derrick Moore and the 
other on a nine-yard pass by Krieg to Herman Moore. 
</P>
<P>
 Krieg completed five of 13 passes for 99 yards and one touchdown. Running Wild 
</P>
<P>
 The top single-game rushing performances in NFL history: 05,16,18,05,05,04 
Date Player Car Yds TD Nov. 20, 1977 Walter Payton 40 275 1 Nov. 25, 1976 O.J. 
Simpson 29 273 2 Sept. 16, 1973 O.J. Simpson 29 250 2 Dec. 5, 1971 Willie 
Ellison 26 247 1 Dec. 8, 1963 Cookie Gilchrist 36 243 5 Nov. 11, 1994 Barry 
Sanders 26 237 0 Oct. 31, 1993 Emmitt Smith 30 237 1 Nov. 19, 1961 Jim Brown 34 
237 4 Nov. 24, 1957 Jim Brown 31 237 4 Sept. 22, 1963 Jim Brown 20 232 2 Nov. 
15, 1959 Bobby Mitchell 14 232 3  
</P>
