<P>
KELLEY GOING TO SAN DIEGO STATE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Trabuco Hills' Ryan Kelley, the Pacific Coast League's most valuable player in 
baseball, has signed a letter of intent to play for San Diego State. 
</P>
<P>
 The right-handed pitcher, a second-team Times all-county selection, had a 10-3 
record and a 1.09 earned-run average for the Mustangs, who won the league 
title. 
</P>
