<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL 1994-1995 / CENTURY LEAGUE; 1993-94 IN REVIEW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Standings 05,18,05,05,05,06 *2*League *2*Overall School W L W L Santa Ana 
Valley 9 1 26 4 Orange 9 1 23 4 Foothill 5 5 11 16 Canyon 4 6 9 13 El Modena 3 
7 9 17 Villa Park 0 10 3 20 Highlights 
</P>
<P>
 Two intense showdowns led to a co-championship between Orange and Santa Ana 
Valley, two of the top teams in Orange County last season. Orange won the first 
meeting, at its itsy-bitsy, storage-room-of-a-gymnasium. Gil Gonzales scored 22 
points and Pat Harris 19 in a 64-58 victory. Olujimi Mann, Santa Ana Valley's 
standout point guard, had his worst night of the season. He made six of 19 
shots and was 0 for 8 in the fourth quarter. Mann and Co. got their revenge in 
the regular-season finale. Mann scored 28 points in the 64-41 rout. He scored 
14 in the third quarter, including a variety of dunks, as the Falcons blew the 
game open. Santa Ana Valley's success continued into the playoffs. The Falcons 
reached the Southern Section Division I-AA semifinals, where they lost, 69-67, 
to La Crescenta Crescenta Valley. Mann had 30 points, including eight 
three-pointers, six assists, four steals and two blocks. Orange reached the 
quarterfinals of the 1 -- A playoffs, but lost to Edison, 63-53. Harris had 21 
points, but Gonzales scored only four. He had 24 in the previous game, a 69-61 
victory over Corona. Foothill qualified for the III-A playoffs, but lost to 
top-seeded Sonora, 71-48, in the first round. Mann averaged 21.9 points, 7.2 
assist and 6.6 rebounds. Gonzales averaged 14.3 points and made 79 
three-pointers to give him 171 for his career. Both were named first-team 
All-Orange County. 
</P>
