<P>
PEOPLE: ROCKWELL NAMES WILLIAM CALISE AS SENIOR VICE PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 William J. Calise Jr., 56, has been appointed senior vice president, general 
counsel and secretary of Rockwell International Corp. He succeeds Charles H. 
Harff, 65, who said he will retire from the Seal Beach-based diversified 
high-technology company late next year.Harff will continue until that time as 
senior vice president and special counsel. Calise was previously a partner with 
the law firm of Chadbourne & Parke, and was a member of the firm's management 
committee. In addition, John R. Stocker, 52, was appointed vice president-law 
and corporate officer. Stocker will report to Calise and will oversee legal 
matters affecting the firm's aerospace and government businesses. 
