<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAKING IT IN O.C.; FIRM RE-CREATES MUSEUM-QUALITY FRAMES FOR ART 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Riegler & Sons Gilded Designs in Huntington Beach produces authentic, handmade 
re-creations of period picture frames. 
</P>
<P>
 Owned by Peter and Diane Riegler, the company has 11 employees who use 
old-fashioned woodworking techniques to produce nearly 500 kinds of frames, 
including Italian, French, Spanish and American styles. The museum-quality 
frames are produced in a 9,000-square-foot plant. 
</P>
<P>
 Craftsmen mill, join, carve and gild frames to order for customers. Co-owner 
Peter Riegler began designing and creating his own picture frames while still a 
student at the Cleveland Institute of Art. 
</P>
<P>
 Riegler & Sons moved to Huntington Beach in 1992 after six years in Laguna 
Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 If your company is Making It in O.C., please let us know. Call (714) 966-5950. 
 
</P>
</TEXT>
