<P>
 Kmart Will Open Two Superstores: Kmart Corp., the nation's second-largest 
retailer, will introduce its superstore concept this week to a Southern 
California retail market that is increasingly embracing the concept of one-stop 
shopping. The first of the Super Kmart stores in the region will open Sunday in 
Anaheim and La Habra.The stores incorporate a regular Kmart with a full-service 
grocery featuring fresh and gourmet foods. They also include pharmacies, floral 
departments, video rentals and restaurant areas. About 600 full- and part-time 
employees will work at each of the stores, which will be open 24 hours a day. 
Kmart has about 70 superstores nationwide. The first in California opened in 
September in Fresno. The company, which has said it expects to report its 
seventh straight quarterly earnings decline for the third quarter, has been on 
a massive self-improvement program this year to shore up its retailing 
operation, including overhauling store concepts and remodeling. 
